4:
Cleaned up that quest pretty fast,
did you? Well, here's payment.
Keep up the good work, Stella.
13:
Yes, that's the one. Do you know
what's happened to them?
15:
The Swallow Knights, eh? Well, there's
a name I haven't heard in a while.
16:
They've disappeared. Swallowed up
by the Kaleidoscope, no doubt.
23:
Sorry to keep you waiting, Stella...
Everything's all right now. Let's go.
30:
We're being followed.
Who's there? Show yourself!
33:
Yuwel... It's really you, isn't it? It's me.
Don't tell me you've forgotten
poor William!
43:
Yes, but the Swallow Knights...
We all broke up and scattered.
I'm sorry, Yuwel...
46:
Don't be. The cracks in our fellowship
formed long ago...
even when I was there.
49: Are you going to go on fighting?
56: I am all the Swallow Knights have left.
64:
I don't know...
He WAS once a comrade.
67:
Would you mind
telling me the full story?
70: No, but... It's a long and bitter tale.
73:
A long way from Palpebra, there lies
a place called the Farlands. It's ruled
by a king and Nine Noble Houses,
and it's where I was born.
75:
Some time ago, monsters began
crawling into our towns and cities.
Each year, the bodies of those slain
by their claws grew higher and higher.
77:
But the nobles only stood by
and watched... It was unbearable.
79:
I gathered to me a group of warriors.
Fighters, who would use their swords
for the people. And that was the start
of the Swallow Knights.
81:
But, well... what power can such
a ragged band wield? Our funds soon
ran short, and we were driven into
the Kaleidoscope, seeking treasure.
83:
...Funny, isn't it? We had hoped
the labyrinth would save us, but it's
what delivered the final blow.
91:
While I was gone,
the Swallow Knights disbanded.
It was for the best, I suppose...
98:
It was saved... if you can call it that.
The king's family learned that
the Kaleidoscope was the source of its
troubles, and demanded reparations.
100:
In place of money, Palpebra shared all
that it knew about the Kaleidoscope.
Armed with this knowledge, the nobles
waged war on the monsters...
and banished them from our lands.
107:
Yes. Until the day all suffering has
ended, I will not lay down my sword.
120: Light said you remind him of himself.
122:
Alk found the idea funny, but now,
I see what Light meant.
125: You do? Heh... Well, thank you.
127:
...I can't let my journey end before
I've lived up to those words.
131:
Yep. Now stop planning your
retirement, and come eat dinner.
135:
Retirement?
I never said a word about retirement!
...How long have you been there?
138:
Long enough to be STARVING.
Come on, Yuwel... Light's waiting.
141: *sigh* Life is never dull with you, Alk.
